    "sections": {
        "description": "<p>Shortcode for the official Twitter Widgets.</p>\n<p>Insert Twitter Widgets in content using a simple customizable shortcode.<br />\nSupported widgets: Profile, Search, Favorites.</p>\n<h4>Contacts</h4>\n<p>&#8220;Contatti&#8221; here: <a href=\"http://www.starsailor.it/info/\" rel=\"nofollow ugc\">http://www.starsailor.it/info/</a></p>\n",
        "installation": "<ol>\n<li>Upload <code>tw-shortcode</code> directory to the <code>/wp-content/plugins/</code> directory.</li>\n<li>Activate the plugin through the &#8216;Plugins&#8217; menu in WordPress.</li>\n<li>Go to Options -&gt; Tw Shortcode and customize all you need.</li>\n</ol>\n",
        "faq": "\n<h4>What&#8217;s the shortcode to show the widget?</h4>\n<p>\n<p>Simply put:<br />\n    [tw]<br />\nin your content to show custom settings from the admin panel.</p>\n</p>\n<h4>Can i override these?</h4>\n<p>\n<p>Yes. Available custom options are:<br />\n    [tw type&#8221;{$}&#8221; search&#8221;{$}&#8221; title&#8221;{$}&#8221; subject&#8221;{$}&#8221; width&#8221;{$}&#8221; height&#8221;{$}&#8221;]<br />\n{$} = your custom setting</p>\n</p>\n\n",
        "changelog": "<h4>0.9 (26/11/2011)</h4>\n<ul>\n<li>First public release.</li>\n<li>Insert Twitter Widgets in content.</li>\n<li>Supported widgets: Profile, Search, Favorites.</li>\n</ul>\n"
    },
